\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Policy Manual is a living governance instrument that requires structured review,
 controlled change,
 and periodic institutional reaffirmation to remain current,
 enforceable,
 and aligned with legal,
 operational,
 and institutional realities.
 This policy defines the mechanisms through which the manual is maintained,
 updated,
 and reauthorized.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Review Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
To ensure continued relevance and compliance,
 all policies within the Information Operations Policy Manual shall undergo the following review cycles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Annual Internal Review
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall conduct an annual internal review of each policy to evaluate compliance,
 technical accuracy,
 and workforce awareness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Biennial Resanction
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall coordinate biennial resanction of the Policy Manual with the County Manager and,
 where required,
 the Board of County Commissioners.
 The Policy Manual remains in force during a lapsed resanction period;
 policies do not expire for a lack of resanction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Timeline Deviations
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall document deviations from scheduled review timelines,
 including justification and a revised review date,
 in the System of Engagement within five (5) business days of the missed deadline.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Ad Hoc Reviews
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall initiate ad hoc reviews when triggered by:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Regulatory or legal changes (e.g.,
 
\series bold
CJIS
\series default
 Security Policy updates,
 HIPAA requirements,
 or 
\series bold
NRS
\series default
 amendments).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Internal or external audit findings.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Major incidents or critical system events requiring post-mortem policy adjustment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Significant organizational changes (e.g.,
 departmental mergers or new mandates).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Significant technology changes (e.g.,
 new platforms,
 major infrastructure shifts).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
