\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Technical Directives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director may issue Technical Directives when standard policies obstruct legal compliance,
 operational integrity,
 or incident response.
 The underlying policy provision remains in force except to the extent specifically modified by the Technical Directive.
 Expiration or rescission of a Technical Directive restores the original provision without further action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Permissible Scenarios
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A CJIS,
 HIPAA,
 or statutory compliance deadline requiring immediate action.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Response to a zero-day vulnerability or active threat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Critical failure affecting escalation,
 access control,
 or operational procedures.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Documentation Requirements
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall document each Technical Directive in the System of Engagement immediately upon issuance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The documentation shall include justification,
 scope,
 and a specific expiration date.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automatic Expiration
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Each Technical Directive shall expire ninety (90) calendar days after issuance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Upon expiration,
 the IT Director shall either incorporate the Technical Directive into a formally approved policy revision under Section 6.2 or explicitly rescind it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall document each rescission in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director shall obtain formal adoption through the standard approval process before re-issuing the same or substantially similar Technical Directive within twelve (12) months of expiration.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Scope Boundary
\series default
:
 Each Technical Directive shall preserve budget authority and the core governance roles defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.06"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (IT Governance and Oversight Structure).
\end_layout

